 1129
Your Honor,

I, Aleksander Nowak, am appearing before this honorable court today to plead guilty to the charge of assault. I acknowledge and take full responsibility for my actions, which caused harm to my employee.

On the day in question, my emotions got the better of me due to my employee's severe mistake at work. Recognizing the significant financial impact it would have on my company, I allowed anger to consume me, ultimately leading to the unfortunate incident. I pushed my employee to the ground and proceeded to kick him in the stomach.

However, I want to emphasize that my immediate regret and remorse were evident after this regrettable incident. Understanding the gravity of my actions, I took immediate steps to ensure the safety and well-being of the victim. I swiftly brought him to the nearest emergency room, ensuring he received the necessary medical attention.

I would like to express my deepest apologies to the victim and his family for the pain and distress I have caused. I realize that my behavior was inexcusable and entirely contrary to any sense of professionalism or humanity. 

In an effort to reconcile my wrongdoing, I have made arrangements to cover the remainder of the victim's hospital bills. It is my genuine hope that this gesture of compensation can alleviate some of the financial burden that he and his family may have faced.

Moreover, I wish to bring to the court's attention that I am a 40-year-old individual with no prior criminal record. This demonstrates that my actions on that fateful day were an aberration, rather than a reflection of my character or moral compass.

I stand before this court humbled by my actions and prepared to accept the consequences of my crime. I understand that by pleading guilty, I have acknowledged my fault, which is, in itself, a mitigating factor. 

Your Honor, I ask you to consider the circumstances leading to this offense, the absence of any prior wrongdoing on my part, and my immediate efforts to rectify the situation as mitigating factors. I assure the court that I have been greatly affected by the repercussions of my actions and have taken the necessary steps to prevent such an incident from happening again.

In conclusion, I plead guilty to the charge of assault, accepting full responsibility for my actions. I am deeply remorseful for the harm I caused and the pain I inflicted. I pledge to learn from this experience and contribute positively to society, should the court afford me the opportunity.

Thank you for your attention, Your Honor.

